{
  "texts": [
    "The TiO 2 primarily absorbs UV light due to its wide bandgap.",
    "Photosensitizers, on the other hand, can absorb light in a broader range, including visible light (Tinoco Navarro and Jaroslav, 2023; Yu et al., 2022).",
    "Through coupling a photosensitizer with TiO 2, the composite photocatalyst becomes capable of utilizing a wider spectrum of sunlight, making it more efficient under natural light conditions.",
    "The photosensitizers can facilitate the separation of photoinduced electron-hole pairs more effectively (Pawar et al., 2018).",
    "When light is absorbed by the photosensitizer, it generates an excited state with an electron at a higher energy level."
  ]
}